               (Translation: P. L. Bat. 25.31)
<milestone unit="line" n="1" rend="break"/>Asclepiades greets his dearest Demosthenes. 
<milestone unit="line" n="4" rend="break"/>Dius also called . . . .us, who brings you this letter, is a friend of mine. So help (?) him in order that (?) he may buy .... Write me back through him on any other matter you need in Ptolemais. And buy me a pair of plain cushions and receive the price from him ....

            </p>
